Interview-ready summary ğŸ”¥

If Redis goes down, Sidekiq cannot enqueue, fetch, retry, or track jobs. Running jobs may finish but wonâ€™t be acknowledged, so they can be re-run after Redis recovers. Once Redis is back, Sidekiq reconnects automatically and resumes processing. Jobs attempted during the outage are lost unless the application handles retries.

One-liner (if interviewer cuts you off)

Redis down means Sidekiq is effectively paused. No Redis, no background jobs.